The paper involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to generate new levels for the first-person shooter game DOOM. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as GANs are a type of machine learning algorithm. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of images and topological features, which suggests that it could also fall under Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the generation of new content, which could fall under Graphics (cs.GR) and Game Theory (cs.GT).
